26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_volt_gpio.c,v 1.3 2018/08/27 07:41:41 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include <subdev/volt.h>
30#include <subdev/bios.h>
31#include <subdev/bios/gpio.h>
32#include <subdev/gpio.h>
33
34#include "priv.h"
35
36static const u8 tags[] = {
37 DCB_GPIO_VID0, DCB_GPIO_VID1, DCB_GPIO_VID2, DCB_GPIO_VID3,
38 DCB_GPIO_VID4, DCB_GPIO_VID5, DCB_GPIO_VID6, DCB_GPIO_VID7,
39};
40
41int
42nvkm_voltgpio_get(struct nvkm_volt *volt)
43{
44 struct nvkm_gpio *gpio = volt->subdev.device->gpio;
45 u8 vid = 0;
46 int i;
47
48 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(tags); i++) {
49 if (volt->vid_mask & (1 << i)) {
50 int ret = nvkm_gpio_get(gpio, 0, tags[i], 0xff);
51 if (ret < 0)
52 return ret;
53 vid |= ret << i;
54 }
55 }
56
57 return vid;
58}
59
60int
61nvkm_voltgpio_set(struct nvkm_volt *volt, u8 vid)
62{
63 struct nvkm_gpio *gpio = volt->subdev.device->gpio;
64 int i;
65
66 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(tags); i++, vid >>= 1) {
67 if (volt->vid_mask & (1 << i)) {
68 int ret = nvkm_gpio_set(gpio, 0, tags[i], 0xff, vid & 1);
69 if (ret < 0)
70 return ret;
71 }
72 }
73
74 return 0;
75}
76
77int
78nvkm_voltgpio_init(struct nvkm_volt *volt)
79{
80 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &volt->subdev;
81 struct nvkm_gpio *gpio = subdev->device->gpio;
82 struct dcb_gpio_func func;
83 int i;
84
85 /* check we have gpio function info for each vid bit. on some
86 * boards (ie. nvs295) the vid mask has more bits than there
87 * are valid gpio functions... from traces, nvidia appear to
88 * just touch the existing ones, so let's mask off the invalid
89 * bits and continue with life
90 */
91 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(tags); i++) {
92 if (volt->vid_mask & (1 << i)) {
93 int ret = nvkm_gpio_find(gpio, 0, tags[i], 0xff, &func);
94 if (ret) {
95 if (ret != -ENOENT)
96 return ret;
97 nvkm_debug(subdev, "VID bit %d has no GPIO\n", i);
98 volt->vid_mask &= ~(1 << i);
99 }
100 }
101 }
102
103 return 0;
104}
